The paper focuses on detecting novel content in large image data sets and providing visual explanations for the same. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. Additionally, the paper employs a convolutional neural network (CNN) for feature extraction, which is a common technique in computer vision research. Therefore, cs.CV is the most likely sub-category. 

The paper also mentions the use of novelty detection methods and the potential discovery of previously unknown phenomena, which suggests that the paper may also belong to the artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-category. 

The paper uses reconstruction error to detect novel content, which is a technique commonly used in machine learning and deep learning research. This suggests that the paper may also belong to the machine learning (cs.LG) sub-category. 

The paper deals with large data sets and the identification of common trends or patterns, which suggests that it may also belong to the information retrieval (cs.IR) sub-category. 

Finally, the paper deals with image data sets, which suggests that it may also belong to the multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category.
